<topic id='class_patient_diagnosis.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Class: PATIENT DIAGNOSIS - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A subtype of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person_property">PERSON PROPERTY</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
Diagnostic observations recorded about a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>.        </p>
      <p>Note:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
A 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient_diagnosis">PATIENT DIAGNOSIS</xref>
 should be classified, where possible, using 
                                <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                        keyref="supporting_definition_international_classification_of_diseases__icd_">International Classification of Diseases (ICD)</xref>
 or other classification codes approved centrally for mapping to 
                                <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                        keyref="supporting_definition_international_classification_of_diseases__icd_">International Classification of Diseases (ICD)</xref>
 codes.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                     keyref="supporting_definition_read_coded_clinical_terms">Read Coded Clinical Terms</xref>
               <p>
 or 
                                <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                        keyref="supporting_definition_snomed_ct">SNOMED CT</xref>
 can be used in addition to 
                                <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                        keyref="supporting_definition_international_classification_of_diseases__icd_">International Classification of Diseases (ICD)</xref>
 codes for 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient_diagnosis">PATIENT DIAGNOSIS</xref>. However 
                                <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                        keyref="supporting_definition_read_coded_clinical_terms">Read Coded Clinical Terms</xref>
 are not accepted for the purposes of central 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_hospital_episode_statistics">Hospital Episode Statistics</xref>
 data, where 
                                <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                        keyref="supporting_definition_international_classification_of_diseases__icd_">International Classification of Diseases (ICD)</xref>
 is mandatory.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
</body>
